cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computational Linguistics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with spoken language understanding and proposes models to capture contextual information for dialogue understanding. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the proposed models use machine learning techniques to automatically learn the time-decay function and identify the current speaker. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper proposes novel models that use attention mechanisms to capture contextual information. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with spoken language understanding and the models are applied to audio data. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also less likely but possible as the proposed models use neural networks to learn the time-decay function and identify the current speaker.
